{"search_data": "AssamAssam Fee Waiver Scheme 2019 \u2013 Parental Income Limit Hiked for Students Assam Fee Waiver Scheme 2019 parental income limit hiked, students with annual family income less than Rs. 2 lakh can get free admission in UG / PG courses in all provincialized & govt. colleges & 5 universitiesAssam Fee Waiver Scheme 2019The salient features and highlights of the Fee Waiver Scheme Assam are as follows:-If the parents of students are working either in state or central govt. jobs, then their monthly salary slip needs to be produced while taking admission in colleges.In case parents are working in private organization, then salary slip from employer is necessary indicating their salary is less than Rs. 2 lakh p.a.If parents are not working either in govt or private institution or organization, then certificate from the circle officer or mouzader would be considered.In addition to the above 3 conditions, if principal and admission committee in their wisdom feels that the annual family income of student is less than Rs 2 lakh, then concerned principal can provide free admission to those students.Fee Waiver Scheme Assam also covers all the Persons with Disability (PWDs) without any consideration of parental income."}